I think there is some confusion with &#39;Sekibun&#39; and &#39;Akabumi&#39;, these are
alternative readings of the same two kanji, it is now commonly read
&#39;Sekibun&#39;, perhaps the item is signed &#39;Yurakusai Sekibun&#39; which is his
common signature and is very hard to read due to his odd way of  cutting it.
Alan


